exports[`Component: ExtractData should render the correct layout 1`] = `
<Fragment>
  <FrequentlyAskedQuestionsstyles__HelpAnswer>
    <div>
      <p>
        At this stage data is extracted from the document by the selected extraction engine.
      </p>
      <p>
        Data extraction is the key functionality of the DEPS platform.
  DEPS can extract multiple entities from multi-languages documents:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Fields
        </li>
        <li>
          Key-value pairs
        </li>
        <li>
          Blocks of text
        </li>
        <li>
          Complex structure (tables, lists)
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        DEPS can extract several forms of data that have now become relevant for all types of business:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Printed text
        </li>
        <li>
          Hand-printed and handwritten text
        </li>
        <li>
          Images
        </li>
        <li>
          Checkboxes
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Extracting of data usually occurs automatically after the document is loaded and preprocessed if the user
  selects the 'Send for Extraction' check box when uploading documents.
      </p>
    </div>
    <ExtractDatastyles__FirstExtractImage />
  </FrequentlyAskedQuestionsstyles__HelpAnswer>
  <FrequentlyAskedQuestionsstyles__HelpAnswer>
    <div>
      <p>
        To start extracting data, the user also can select the required document on the 'Documents' tab by checking the box
  on the left and selecting the Extract Data action from the panel that appears at the top.
      </p>
      <p>
        Another way to launch data extracting is to open the document, click the button in the right pane, and select the
  Extract Data action from the drop-down list.
      </p>
    </div>
    <ExtractDatastyles__SecondExtractImage />
  </FrequentlyAskedQuestionsstyles__HelpAnswer>
  <ExtractDatastyles__ThirdExtractImage />
</Fragment>
`;
